From: Kamil Lulko <limakzagan@gmail.com>
Subject: win32u/opengl: universal zero-copy GL editor present via AHB bounce

Replace the per-frame glReadPixels + GDI readback in framebuffer_surface_swap
with a UNIVERSAL zero-copy path. The Android system EGL imports AHardwareBuffers
(EGL_ANDROID_image_native_buffer, CDD-mandated) but NOT raw dma-bufs; the wine
surfaceless Mesa EGL exports/imports dma-bufs but can't make AHBs. Bridge:
allocate an AHB (NDK), take its own dma-buf fd (AHardwareBuffer_getNativeHandle->
data[0]), import THAT into Mesa as a renderable FBO (EGL_LINUX_DMA_BUF_EXT —
universal on Mesa), GPU-blit the editor frame into it (vertically flipped for the
top-left AHB convention; imported as ARGB8888 so GL-red lands in the B byte to
match the compositor's .bgr shader), and ship the AHB over the existing AHB
REGISTER/PRESENT side-channel (0048) — the consumer imports it via the existing
(universal) AHB path, no consumer change. CPU_READ usage forces LINEAR so the
producer-side import needs no modifier; the AHB is a separate buffer from the
editor FBO so there is no tearing. Enabled by VSTPOC_AHB_GL=1 (default-on via
WineHostProcess; works in plugin prefixes where VSTPOC_AHB_PRESENT is 0) or
VSTPOC_AHB_PRESENT=1; VSTPOC_AHB_GL=0 forces readback; any failure falls back.
Vendors AhbChannelProtocol.h into win32u (POSIX sockets, no NDK headers).
~0.7 core saved vs readback on Ampbox (Adreno 750). See
feedback_gl_zerocopy_dmabuf_not_ahb.

diff --git a/dlls/win32u/opengl.c b/dlls/win32u/opengl.c
--- a/dlls/win32u/opengl.c
+++ b/dlls/win32u/opengl.c
